column5: Hit Lake O last weekend with with my mate Mike for some late summer Pike. We boated 10 Pike total and missed a few others... Great day! All the fish hit Terminator Spinnerbaits, white and white/chartreusse.
been waiting for a nice report about some Lake O pike - congrats, nice fish
Great report and pictures. Love Pike fishing any time of year!  Thanks for sharing, MTBF
Great job guys    Awesome gators Thanks for sharing Leechman
nice report - those are some beauty  gators.
Great Report, thanx for sharing, I'd like to try the islands from my boat again some time Richard
Great report. That 3rd one is a solid fish!Did you weigh it?

Johnny Bass, I didn't weigh it but I'd give it a good 14 to 15lbs, it was a really thick fish. Also, when looking at the pictures, bare in mind that I'm 6ft 6in and weigh 275lbs, I tend to make any fish look small  Cheers, Shaun
dude, what happpened to the show?? used to love watching it! was always great to see places so close to home and the way u showed what great angling opportunities were in our back yards!

uglyfish, I can't say too much right now but we are working on some ideas to get the show back up and running again. Unfortunately we lost a major sponsor due to a corporate takeover as we began production of season-3 and the funding just wasn't there to get the show to air.  If you're interested you can join our Facebook group for updates etc, I post a lot of reports and videos etc their that you may be interested in.  Here's the link: http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=6426308129&ref=ts  Thanks for your feedback and interest, much appreciated  Cheers, Shaun
some very nice Pike....good luck with whatever is in the works for the show.
"... but I'd give it 14 or 15lbs."  You're delusional!  There's no way it's even 10.
thanks shaun! i joined up. sucks about the sponsor, but glad to hear ur working through it and pushing forward with season 3! all the best bud!
Some nice lookin toothy critters and I'd say the 3'rd pic is around 14 lbs, lol.
